Package org.pepstock.charba.client.impl.plugins.enums

Enum TableauScheme

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TableauScheme>
      • org.pepstock.charba.client.impl.plugins.enums.TableauScheme
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<TableauScheme>, Key, ColorScheme
    public enum TableauScheme
extends Enum<TableauScheme>
    Contains all scheme definitions to map the Tableau schemes.
    To configure ColorSchemes.ID plugin, where category is "tableau".
    Every color scheme has a number at the end of its name, which indicates the number of that colors included in the scheme. If the number of the datasets is larger than it, the same colors will appear repeatedly. A color is not modified if it is specified by dataset options.
    Author:
    Andrea "Stock" Stocchero
